{"author":{"id":"a515054682a3c3a9c544dfef94052699069579917ef4e80f0fa3a051329394b1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1770817512,"nonce":"GabeIkpHoCAd2fI5Bs0BtZOODTw=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s7niVJC","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7670#issuecomment-3884536386"},"message":"\u003e The screenshot shows the html output of the tool? \n\nYes, I think this is from meme-chip html output results. \n1) Click “View” to display the results. \n2) In the results page, click “DREME”. \n3) Click “Submit/Download”. \n4) Click “Tomtom”, then “Submit”.\n\n \u003e Using any functionality of the html page can not work. \n\nOh, how so? \nIn the test-data for meme, there is a case for `tomtom` so I thought that it was supported.\n\n\u003e Do you know if the tool also supports fasta (or any other format useful for downstream processing) output?\n\nFrom https://meme-suite.org/meme/doc/tomtom.html\n```\nInputs\n\u003cquery motif file\u003e\nThe name of a file containing one or more motifs in [MEME format](https://meme-suite.org/meme/doc/meme-format.html) or the HTML (.html) or plain text (.txt) output of MEME, STREME or DREME. Each of these motifs will be searched against the target files. If you only wish to search with a subset of these motifs then look into the -m and -mi options.\n\n\u003ctarget motif file\u003e+\nThe names of one or more files containing [MEME formatted motifs](https://meme-suite.org/meme/doc/meme-format.html). Outputs from MEME, STREME and DREME are supported, as well as Minimal MEME Format. You can convert many other motif formats to MEME format using [conversion scripts](https://meme-suite.org/meme/doc/overview.html#motif_conversion_utilities) available with the MEME Suite.\n```\nDoes not look like so...","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1770817738,"nonce":"8haEYRJTsrsEGe8EJVQT36Yl8Eg=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOAW4Y0s7niVJCzpf_Rtg"},"target":"7444fa79355d13db181310aeac554e1b417eeb05269b4cb44efbcfb9c84476ba","messag